article.headline: Texas moves into tie for second in Big 12
article.linkText: Longhorns split season series with Tech
article.story:
AUSTIN, Texas (Ticker) -- Nina Norman scored 15 points and 
Tiffany Jackson sparked a strong bench effort as No. 17 Texas
posted a 64-43 victory over (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 13 AP) Texas Tech in a Big 12 Conference matchup.

Norman was 6-of-15 from the field and Jackson added 12 rebounds
as the Longhorns avenged a 79-62 loss to the Lady Raiders
on January 12.

Texas (15-7, 8-3 Big 12) is now in a four-way tie for second in
the conference, one game behind eighth-ranked Baylor.

Texas Tech (17-5, 8-3) shot 27 percent (9-for-34) in the first
half and trailed 29-21 at the break. Things did not get any
better in the second half for the Lady Raiders as they shot
9-of-33.

Erin Grant was the lone Texas Tech player in double figures with
10 points.
